column5: If I get my choice,it,s ham,not turkey for Christmas dinner. And I got last say.        It will get sliced up,and covered with a, cherry/pinapple and dry mustard syrup.  Im sure I,ll get my hand slapped a few times for tasting.
Looks good Brian. Debbe insists on Turkey for Thanksgiving and Christmas. I am with you on the ham though,but I've  got the rest of the year to fit my ham and scalloped potatoes in.
I like my turkey Steve,but on the BBQ,or deep fryer.
Try to hold off samplin' it until you've taken an "after" photo.
"Virginia" like the looks of that ham.  Merry Christmas Brian and Family.   Art
all those points it looks a bit like a porkypine...
